</a>=C2=A0It bought a capped profit interest in OpenAI=E2=80=99s capped-pro=
fit subsidiary?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Part of this is for Reason 2: OpenAI is a nonp=
rofit, it has unusual goals, and it is pursuing those goals with an unusual=
 profit-sharing mechanism rather than with normal stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But part of it is for Reason 3, regulatory arb=
itrage. <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33655342.2=
86402/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTItMDgvb=
Wljcm9zb2Z0LXMtYW5zd2VyLXRvLW9wZW5haS1pbnF1aXJ5LWl0LWRvZXNuLXQtb3duLWEtc3Rh=
a2U_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTIxMTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmN=
lPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMjExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB532ae49e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Dina Bass and L=
eah Nylen report</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">With global regulators examining Microsoft Cor=
p.=E2=80=99s $13 billion investment in OpenAI, the software giant has a sim=
ple argument it hopes will resonate with antitrust officials: It doesn=E2=
=80=99t own a traditional stake in the buzzy startup so can=E2=80=99t be sa=
id to control it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When Microsoft negotiated an additional $10 bi=
llion investment in OpenAI in January, it opted for an unusual arrangement,=
 people familiar with the matter said at the time. Rather than buy a chunk =
of the cutting-edge artificial intelligence lab, it cut a deal to receive a=
lmost half of OpenAI=E2=80=99s financial returns until the investment is re=
paid up to a pre-determined cap, one of the people said. The unorthodox str=
ucture was concocted because OpenAI is a capped for-profit company housed i=
nside a non-profit organization.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s not clear regulators see a distin=
ction, however. On Friday the UK Competition and Markets Authority said it =
was gathering information from stakeholders to determine whether the collab=
oration between the two firms threatens competition in the UK, home of Goog=
le=E2=80=99s AI research lab Deepmind. The US Federal Trade Commission is a=
lso examining the nature of Microsoft=E2=80=99s investment in OpenAI and wh=
ether it may violate antitrust laws, according to a person familiar with th=
e matter. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Microsoft didn=E2=80=99t report the transactio=
n to the agency because the investment in OpenAI doesn=E2=80=99t amount to =
control of the company under US law, the person said. OpenAI is a non-profi=
t and acquisitions of non-corporate entities aren=E2=80=99t reported under =
US merger law, regardless of value. Agency officials are analyzing the situ=
ation and assessing what its options are.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWhile details of our agreement remain=
 confidential, it is important to note that Microsoft does not own any port=
ion of OpenAI and is simply entitled to a share of profit distributions,=E2=
=80=9D a Microsoft spokesperson said in a statement.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sure. Ownership of a company consists=C2=A0<em=
>mainly=C2=A0</em>of being entitled to a share of profit distributions, but=
 not=C2=A0<em>only=C2=A0</em>that; ownership does often (<a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33655342.286402/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDctMTEvaW52ZXN0b3JzLWdhdmUtc25=
hcC1hLWdpZnQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMTIxMTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG=
1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMxMjExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0d=
WZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1f0d1870" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">not always</a>) come with, f=
or instance, voting rights. Microsoft has isolated the profit share and tak=
en only that, not actual ownership. Okay fine and also a <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33655342.286402/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3Nq=
LmNvbS90ZWNoL2FpL29wZW5haXMtbmV3LWJvYXJkLXRha2VzLW92ZXItYW5kLXNheXMtbWljcm9=
zb2Z0LXdpbGwtaGF2ZS1vYnNlcnZlci1yb2xlLTUwZTU1Yjcz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB=
6560a677" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;"> board observer seat</a>.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s not clear regulators see=
 a distinction,=E2=80=9D or that they should really. The conceptual overlap=
 between =E2=80=9Cowning a portion of OpenAI=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cbeing en=
titled to a share of profit distributions=E2=80=9D is not perfect, but it i=
s large, and a regulator might reasonably say =E2=80=9Cclose enough.=E2=80=
=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also here is a small fun fact about this disti=
nction. When I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/336=
55342.286402/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMj=
